item.title: End border ‘one-upmanship’: Tas premier
item.description: Tasmanian Premier Peter Gutwein has called for his counterparts to end their one-upmanship around the issue of state border closures.

item.title: Cargo vessel loses 40 containers off NSW
item.description: A Singapore-flagged ship that lost about 40 shipping containers in rough seas off NSW was carrying face masks, household appliances and building materials.

item.title: UK minister resigns over PM adviser
item.description: Douglas Ross, a junior minister in the Scotland Office, has resigned from the UK government over the handling of accusations the prime minister's senior adviser breached the coronavirus lockdown by travelling to get help with childcare.

item.title: Boost for NSW domestic violence services
item.description: NSW domestic violence services are set for a funding boost amid concerns the state has experienced a rise in domestic and family violence during the coronavirus pandemic.

item.title: Man held after disabled Sydney man robbed
item.description: A man has been arrested after he allegedly robbed a wheelchair-bound man in Sydney's CBD.

item.title: US stock futures rise 2 per cent
item.description: US stock futures have risen 2 per cent and breached a major chart barrier as investors brushed aside China-US trade tension and braced for a reopening of the world economy.

item.title: Elderly driver charged over Syd cafe death
item.description: An elderly driver who allegedly killed a woman when his car ploughed into tables outside a Sydney cafe earlier this year has now been charged.

item.title: Search for Melbourne woman over sex crime
item.description: Police are searching for a woman after a "horrific" sex crime was committed on a cognitively impaired woman in her suburban Melbourne home.

item.title: WA man had photos of girls bound, gagged
item.description: A man caught with sexual images of young children, including some who were bound, gagged and obviously distressed, has been sentenced to 14 months in a Western Australian prison.

item.title: Cyber attacks on Red Cross bushfire fund
item.description: The Australian Red Cross has been hit by almost 900 cyber attacks attempting to access the $216 million raised in donations for bushfire victims.
